Meet <b>CharyCute</b>, our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>You might end up running into Chary if you happen to hang out at the Zoo, the Mall, or the Movie Theater. Whether it's animals, shopping, or enjoying cinema, she's always on the go. <br><br>In the midst of her busy schedule, she still makes time for the finer things in life, such as Tricky Touchdown, Home Run Derby, Galactic Defender, and Sink Three. Her trophies for these games have made a shiny addition to her chic house.<br><br>Chary shows off her refined taste in her stylish digs at <a href='/home/?user=chawey'>75296-F Regal Mountain Drive</a> in Westridge. She has a real eye for interior decorating. Each room has it's own theme and is very feng shui, and everything is color coordinated nicely as well creating a sense of harmony. <br><br>Chary must not be too superstitious, because there are black cats throughout her house.  She might as well throw in a few ladders to walk under, or possibly an umbrella to open in doors. Maybe you don't have to worry about bad luck when you improve your karma by helping out the community. Chary also participated in the Peabody Park Clean-Up.<br><br>Whatever you're doing today, take a minute to say hello to Chary and thank her for being such an upstanding citizen.<br></div>
